{
  "stem": "18470.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 260.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we told the Carter administration those are the buildings we wanted.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They looked like Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were red brick.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They had been the stables for the old Treasury.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And the administration was delighted to give them to us because they knew we would come to the realization that we couldn't build in them, which took about a year or two to discover.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And you couldn't do anything with them, because they were landmarked.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So we said to the administration, we'll take them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then we began the process of un-landmarking landmark buildings.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "That took an act of Congress.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Took two years, and it passed unanimously.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They knocked down these ramshackle buildings, and there we were, you know, in the heart of Washington, DC.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then began the arduous process of planning and fundraising and designing the museum, which was largely designed by Holocaust survivors.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were tremendous political issues that had to be faced, because there were other victims of the Holocaust, of World War II, who wanted representation in the museum.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Among them were Gypsies, the Gypsy community.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There were representatives of the gay communities.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There were outrageous requests by the Ukrainians, who claimed to be victims of the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And a whole series of political involvements, which have not written-- which have not been accurately portrayed yet in the published materials, the tabletop books, that have been written about the museum.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[LAUGHTER]",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
